        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 3:40PM MDT by NWS Riverton WY</headline>
        <description>At 340 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles south of Meeteetse, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of north central Hot
Springs, northwestern Washakie and far southeastern Park Counties,
including the following locations... Badlands Overlook.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
